### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: 5.2.0
(possibly a later version, but this is what I was running successfully - not sure when the bug was re-introduced)


### Description

"@types/node" is being included in node_modules (again). This unfortunately overrides some default types, including setTimeout / setInterval return of type number, instead making the IDE think the return type is NodeJS.Timeout.

The dependency tree or requires is as follows...
@angular-devkit/build-angular
license-webpack-plugin
@types/webpack-sources
@types/node

This has come up at least once before, and was fixed (the angular package causing @types/node to be imported was fixed).

